{
  "patchId": "mass-entity-manager-extended",
  "description": "Add snapshot/restore methods to FMassEntityManager: DestroyEntity(bSignalObservers), BuildEntity(ChunkIndex), DestroyAllEntities, RestoreEntitySerialNumber, GetEntityData, shared fragment value map/hash/reset helpers, archetype chunk accessors, deterministic GetStructCrc32, and DefaultSharedFragments caching for reset-to-default support. Also restores legacy Mass hash-only shared fragment identity in TSharedFragmentsContainer::FindOrAdd (matches pre-5.8 MassExtended behavior): once a shared fragment is created for a given CRC hash, subsequent GetOrCreateSharedFragment calls with the same hash reuse that instance even if its value has since mutated, instead of comparing current memory via CompareScriptStruct and creating a duplicate instance when it no longer matches the freshly-constructed default value. This fixes non-deterministic duplicate shared fragment instances (e.g. FCCRHeatMapSharedFragment) when multiple archetypes lazily request the same shared fragment type after the first instance has already been mutated by gameplay code.",
  "plugin": "Recall",
